  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The developement results in the conversion of the lower ground floor flat consisting of less than 150m2 which is not unsuitable for family accommodation and would result in an unsatisfactory unit mix with an over provision of 1-person/studio flats within the property.  The development would therefore result in harm to the choice of housing stock within the borough. The proposal is therefore contrary to Policy DMH2 of the DMPD (2016) and policy LP26 of the PVLP (2022).  ",
    "Reason : 2 - The development, by reason of poor levels of daylight and outlook and privacy provision, and inadequate Gross Internal Area and ceiling height, results in an unacceptable standard of accommodation for future occupiers. Studio 1 has poor levels of outlook and has failed to demonstrate satisfactory internal daylight would be achieved, Studio 2 has poor level of privacy and Studios 2, 3 and Flat 5 fail to comply with Technical Housing Standards - Nationally Described Space Standard 2015. Overall, the application fails to comply with DMPD (2016) policies DMH4 and DMH6, PVLP (2022) policy LP27 and the Technical Housing Standards - Nationally Described Space Standard 2015. ",
    "Reason : 3 - In dealing with this application the Council has implemented the requirement in the National Planning Policy Framework to work with the applicant in a positive and proactive manner and the Council has, as far as practicable, sought solutions to problems arising in relation to dealing with the planning application. We have made available detailed advice in the form of our statutory policies in the Local Plan consisting of the Core Strategy, Development Management Policies Document, Supplementary Planning documents and where appropriate the Site Specific Allocations Document as well as offering a full pre application advice service. However, we have been unable to seek solutions to problems as the principle of the proposal is clearly contrary to our statutory policies and negotiation could not overcome the reasons for refusal."
  ],
